results.name: Number of noncommutative rings with n elements.
comment: a(n)=0 if and only if n is squarefree.
link: Gregory Dresden, Rings of Size Four, demonstrating that a(4)=2.
example: For n=8, there are 52 rings of order 8, 18 of which are noncommutative, so a(8)=18.
